songs.title: Time Flies
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: FourtyEight]
Run that money counter baby
Forty-Eight

[Hook]
We do whatever for the cheddar, know that cash rules. (Cash)
I pray tomorrow gets better, no more bad news. (Bad)
How they gonna go smile in your face and then go bash you
So many scars from the lies, they like tattoos

[Verse]
Ain't got no time for catching feelings, I rather catch flights
And if I'm taking off the ceiling, then I'm running all the lights
We after 12 like its midnight
I don't know what fake feel like
My neck yeah that real ice
Some things that I realize
This shit just don't feel right
I got problems in real life
I act like it's all right
Regardless I live life

[Bridge]
Walk around with it, but you ain't gon' squeeze
Some of my dogs in prison and they can't go free
Every day Thanksgiving, I keep macs on me. (and cheese)
I know I've been sinning, ya'll pray for me

[Hook]
We do whatever for the cheddar, know that cash rules. (Cash)
I pray tomorrow gets better, no more bad news. (Bad)
How they gonna go smile in your face and then go bash you
So many scars from the lies, they like tattoos
I told my jeweler [?] the rollie, that's how time flies
I'm probably fucking on your bitch on your timeline
I get caught doing the right thing, at the wrong the time
I swear those people will change on you, for those dead guys
